cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper proposes a distributed algorithm that can be interpreted as a network of spiking neurons, suggesting a connection to neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The algorithm is designed to solve the problem of computing sparse representations, which is a common problem in machine learning and signal processing (cs.LG). The algorithm involves communication between nodes, which suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the numerical performance of the algorithm, which suggests a connection to mathematical modeling and simulation (cs.MM).
